QuestionText: Which of the following is NOT a type of machine learning?
What does 'overfitting' in machine learning mean?
OptionA: When the model fits the training data but fails to generalize to new data
OptionB: When the model perfectly fits both training and test data
OptionC: When the model does not perform inference quickly enough
OptionD: When the model cannot learn from training data
CorrectAnswer: When the model fits the training data but fails to generalize to new data

QuestionText: Which algorithm is commonly used for dimensionality reduction?
What is the primary purpose of an activation function in neural networks?
OptionA: To add bias to the input data
OptionB: To introduce non-linearity to the model
OptionC: To normalize the outputs of the model
CorrectAnswer: To introduce non-linearity to the model

QuestionText: Which of the following methods is typically used to prevent overfitting in deep learning?
